INFORMATION COLLECTION AND USE
When we use the Application, we collect several different types of Information for various purposes to provide the Application services
                and improve the Application for you as detailed in section 4 below. By visiting/accessing the Application and/or using the services,
                you agree to provide us with Information as detailed in clause 4 and 5 below, and you are consenting us to use the Information in accordance
                with this Privacy Policy.
TYPES OF DATA COLLECTED
In order to provide you with the best in class Application usage, we require certain Information from you.
                JML may collect the following types of Information:
"Personal Information"
means any information that relates to a natural person, which,
                        either directly or indirectly, in combination with other information available or likely 
                        to be available with JML is capable of identifying such person. It shall also include name,
                        SIM information, mobile number.
"Non-Personal Information"
which shall mean information that does not identify you or any other individual, 
                            and includes session, web beacons and usage data (including type of content accessed on the Application), location, microphone,
                            log data and aggregate information. We use this information to, inter-alia, deliver to you upon your request 
                            our Application tailored for your interests, to measure traffic within our Application, to improve the Application's quality,
                            functionality and interactivity and let advertisers know the geographic locations of our user.
"Telemetry Data"
which shall mean all information and data that the Application
                            generates in connection with your usage, including but not limited to, network policy, log and configuration information;
                            threat intelligence data, , URLs/applications metadata or net flow data; origin and nature of malware;
                            the types of software or applications installed on a network/Device or an endpoint; information about the Devices connected to a network;
                            information generated by sensors, Devices and machinery; information related to the usage, origin of use, 
                            traffic patterns or behaviour of the users of a network or Application; and information relating to the existence of Cookies and other similar applications.
"Tracking Cookies Data/Cookies"
shall mean the cookies and similar tracking technologies
                            to track the activity on Application. Cookies are files with a small amount of data which may include an anonymous unique identifier.
                            The tracking technologies are also used such as beacons, tags and scripts to collect and track information and to improve and analyse Application.
Examples of Cookies we use:
Session Cookies: We use Session Cookies to operate Application and record your sessions of usage of the Application.
Preference Cookies: We use Preference Cookies to remember your preferences and various settings and may enable them for subsequent use.
Security Cookies: We use Security Cookies for Application security purposes.
Advertising Cookies: Advertising Cookies are used to serve you with advertisements that may be relevant to you and your interests, 
                                    if enabled by us. The above shall be collectively referred to as 'Information/Data'.
All the Data collected from you is stored securely on a server(and will not be accessible by other user)
                        operated and managed by JML("Server").
We may place both permanent and temporary Cookies in your Device's.Information collected by Cookies and other technologies 
                            are treated as non-personal information. However, to the extent that IP addresses or similar identifiers 
                            are considered personal information by local law, we treat any information linked to such identifiers as personal information. 
                            Similarly, to the extent that Non-Personal Information is combined with Personal Information, we will treat the combined information as Personal Information.
JML may install Cookies or other similar data collection software in your Device to collect certain Non-Personal 
                            Information and you hereby consent to the same. We may use Cookies, beacons or similar electronic tools to collect 
                            Information to assign each visitor of the Application a unique, random number as a User Identification to understand
                            the user's individual interests using the identified computer.This information of each Application user is stored on the Server
                            will be hashed with a unique Jio digital id(Jio ID).  A cookie cannot read data off your hard drive.
You represent that the Information or Data you provide on the Application is and shall be correct, 
                        current and updated and you have all the rights, permissions and consents to provide such Information or Data, 
                        You warrant and represent that your provision of the Information or Data and JML's consequent storage, collection, 
                        usage, transfer, access, or processing or deletion of the same shall not be in violation of any third-party agreement,
                        laws, judgments, orders or decrees.
